original: Lindberg, Birgit Elisabet, läroverksadjunkt, Värnamo, f. 13/2/09 i Västervik av pastor Theodor Wennström o. Rut Johansson. G. 41 m. lärov:adj. Alvar Lindberg. Barn: Åke f. 42, Lars 44. — Stud:ex. i Upps. 29, fil. mag. där 34, provår v. Hvit-feldtska h. a. 1. i Gbg 40-41. E. o. lär. i 0’sby 35-38, e. adj. i Vadstena 38-39, e. lär. v. Falu folksk:sem. 39-40, e. adj. v. Värnamo samrealsk. 41-43, timlär. där o. e. o. adj. sed. 45, timlär. v. Värnamo yrkessk. 44-45. Res. t. Engl. 34, Tyskl. 37 o. Frankr. 38.
translated:
Lindberg, Birgit Elisabet, school teacher, Värnamo, born on February 13, 1909 in Västervik, to Pastor Theodor Wennström and Rut Johansson. Married in 1941 to school teacher Alvar Lindberg. Children: Åke, born in 1942, Lars, born in 1944. 

Education: Completed secondary school exam in Uppsala in 1929, obtained a Bachelor's degree there in 1934. Completed a probationary year at Hvitfeldtska high school in Gothenburg from 1940-1941. Temporary teacher in 0sby from 1935-1938, assistant teacher in Vadstena from 1938-1939, teacher at Falu primary school seminary from 1939-1940, assistant teacher at Värnamo secondary school from 1941-1943, part-time teacher there and assistant teacher since 1945. Part-time teacher at Värnamo vocational school from 1944-1945. Traveled to England in 1934, Germany in 1937, and France in 1938.
